  <h2>Colour Consultation: The Step Most People Skip</h2>

  <p>Choosing paint colours from chips under store lighting is one of the most unreliable ways to make a decision that will affect you every day. Before committing to a full room, we strongly recommend:</p>

  <ol>
    <li>Purchase 2–3 sample pots of your shortlisted colours</li>
    <li>Paint a 30 × 30 cm swatch directly on the wall (or on a large white card you can move around)</li>
    <li>Observe the swatch at different times of day — morning light, afternoon sun, artificial evening light</li>
    <li>Live with the swatches for 2–3 days before deciding</li>
  </ol>

  <p>We include colour consultation as part of every <a href="/services/painting">painting project</a> — our team can help you navigate the decision and avoid costly repaints.</p>

